WEBVTT

00:06.291 --> 00:08.291
-Nice of you to finally join us,
Amanda-Susan.

00:08.333 --> 00:10.500
-You're welcome, Mr. D.
-[Charlie laughs]

00:10.542 --> 00:12.959
-Oh, you think Amanda-Susan's
funny?

00:13.000 --> 00:14.875
-It's ASS.
-Excuse me?!

00:14.917 --> 00:18.542
-My full name is: Amanda-Susan
Sullivan. But my friends call
me ASS.

00:18.583 --> 00:22.125
-I'm pretty sure that's not
why they call you 'ass'...Ass.

00:22.166 --> 00:24.875
-I said my friends, call me ASS.

00:24.917 --> 00:27.000
-[Class giggles]

00:27.041 --> 00:29.208
-[Gerry]: Alright, well I don't
like your tone.

00:29.250 --> 00:31.875
So you just bought yourself,
a Saturday detention.

00:31.917 --> 00:36.000
-[Mutters]: Eat my shorts.
-What was that?

00:36.041 --> 00:39.250
-Eat. My. Shorts.

00:39.291 --> 00:41.458
-Reference is a little dated.

00:41.500 --> 00:44.125
But you just got yourself
another Saturday detention.

00:44.166 --> 00:47.083
-I'm crushed.
-And that gets you another one,
right there.

00:47.125 --> 00:49.291
-Great, I'm free the
Saturday after that.

00:49.333 --> 00:52.166
Beyond that I'm gonna have
to check my calendar.

00:52.208 --> 00:54.417
-You've got another one.
I can keep going.

00:54.458 --> 00:56.667
-Great, I could do this
all day, Bud!

00:56.709 --> 00:59.083
-And that's another one.
Are you through?

00:59.125 --> 01:01.125
-No!
-And another one.

01:01.166 --> 01:04.458
-So!
-You do realize what's
going on here, right?

01:04.500 --> 01:06.834
-Yes!
-Cut it out, ASS.

01:06.875 --> 01:10.083
-I'd cut it out. Nothin' left
to say, Amanda-Susan?

01:13.291 --> 01:16.250
I didn't think so.
I win.

01:16.291 --> 01:18.208
Back to work.

01:18.250 --> 01:21.500
I will write some things on the
board here, I'd like you to
copy into your...

01:26.041 --> 01:28.458
Did you just throw a shoe at me?
-No.

01:28.500 --> 01:31.250
-Then how come there's one
shoe missing from your foot?

01:34.291 --> 01:36.375
[♪ Music]
-Okay.

01:36.417 --> 01:39.041
♪ I'm awesome, no you're
not dude, don't lie ♪

01:39.083 --> 01:41.667
♪ I'm awesome, I'm driving
around in my mom's ride ♪

01:41.709 --> 01:45.959
♪ I'm awesome, a quarter
of my life gone by ♪

01:46.000 --> 01:48.375
♪ I'm awesome ♪

01:48.417 --> 01:51.792
-[Natalie]: Please, Mr. Cheeley.
You have to reconsider.
I'll be ruined.

01:51.834 --> 01:54.125
-Sorry Natalie, I've already
made my mind up.

01:54.166 --> 01:56.333
-What's going on?
-Not to worry Ms. Mason.

01:56.375 --> 01:58.542
-Pretty sure we have it
all under control.

01:58.583 --> 02:00.834
-He suspended me
for a whole week!

02:00.875 --> 02:03.291
I'll never get into a good
school with that blight on
my record.

02:03.333 --> 02:06.166
And...one little slip up and
everything I've worked for...

02:06.208 --> 02:08.417
[Snaps fingers]:
Is up in flames.

02:08.458 --> 02:11.417
-I think a suspension is a
little extreme, don't you?

02:11.458 --> 02:13.834
-You don't even know
what she did.

02:13.875 --> 02:15.792
It was disgusting!

02:15.834 --> 02:18.208
-Ya know, I think Natalie's
earned a bit of leeway,

02:18.250 --> 02:20.125
don't you, Mr. Cheeley?

02:20.166 --> 02:23.667
Maybe we can change that
suspension to a detention?

02:23.709 --> 02:26.125
-You're the boss.
-Really!?

02:26.166 --> 02:28.291
-Well...
-Thank you!

02:28.333 --> 02:30.834
-[Lisa]: I am the boss.
-[Natalie]: Thank you so much!

02:30.875 --> 02:33.417
[Natalie and Lisa laugh]

02:34.166 --> 02:36.792
-[Laughs]: Ohhhh.

02:36.834 --> 02:40.250
-[Laughs]: Ohhhh.

02:40.291 --> 02:42.583
-[Lisa]: Oh, Gerry?
I just wanted to confirm

02:42.625 --> 02:45.041
that you're covering Saturday
detention.

02:45.083 --> 02:47.458
-Ha!
-Gerry, I'm not asking.

02:47.500 --> 02:50.000
I'm telling you.
-Oh come on, Lisa.

02:50.041 --> 02:52.875
Not this Saturday. It's our
annual baseball draft,

02:52.917 --> 02:55.917
with all my friends. Okay?
I have to be there live,

02:55.959 --> 02:58.583
to pick my players otherwise I
get the crappy auto picks.

02:58.625 --> 03:01.625
-Gerry, there is a system.
Okay? A rotation.

03:01.667 --> 03:03.834
And this week, it's your turn.

03:03.875 --> 03:06.041
-You know this Saturday
detention thing you've added?

03:06.083 --> 03:08.250
You're punishing the teachers,
not the students.

03:08.291 --> 03:10.500
-It's your turn, end of
discussion.

03:10.542 --> 03:12.709
-Can you believe I have
to work Saturday?

03:12.750 --> 03:14.875
-I dream of the day I can take
one day off.

03:14.917 --> 03:17.458
-How come every time I have
something to tell you...

03:17.500 --> 03:21.166
It becomes about you?
Did ya ever listen to yourself?

03:21.208 --> 03:23.250
-Why don't you go fuck
yourself?

03:23.291 --> 03:26.709
[♪ Music]
-[Simon V.O]: Xavier Academy.
Saturday morning.

03:26.750 --> 03:28.917
[Simon V.O]: Almost, nine AM.

03:28.959 --> 03:31.667
[Simon V.O]: The familiar smell
of the halls.

03:31.709 --> 03:34.125
[Simon V.O]: I look around
and I can't help wondering,

03:34.166 --> 03:36.625
[Simon V.O]: who do these people
think they are?

03:36.667 --> 03:39.000
[Simon V.O]: Maybe they see
themselves in the simplest
terms,

03:39.041 --> 03:41.250
[Simon V.O]: the most convenient
definitions.

03:41.291 --> 03:43.625
[Simon V.O]: A princess...

03:43.667 --> 03:46.458
♪ Music
Don't you (Forget About Me)
By: Simple Minds

03:46.500 --> 03:48.667
[Simon V.O]: An athlete.

03:48.709 --> 03:51.125
[♪ Music]
[Car brakes screech]

03:51.166 --> 03:54.000
[♪ Music]
-[Simon V.O]: A criminal.

03:54.041 --> 03:56.125
♪ Music

03:56.166 --> 03:58.792
-[Simon V.O]: A brain.

03:58.834 --> 04:02.083
♪ Music

04:02.125 --> 04:05.542
♪ Music

04:05.583 --> 04:08.083
And a basket case.

04:09.166 --> 04:12.250
-Bye, sweetie. Give mommy
a kiss.

04:12.291 --> 04:15.125
Oh! Way to peel out Petey!

04:15.166 --> 04:18.000
-[Simon V.O]: At least that's
how I saw them all...

04:18.041 --> 04:20.792
-[Simon V.O]: At the beginning.
[Music stops]

04:20.834 --> 04:23.375
-Okay, I just need you to wait
here ten minutes.

04:23.417 --> 04:26.291
I'm gonna run in,
I'll be right back.
-Nope. No, I am not doing that.

04:26.333 --> 04:28.291
-Why not?
-Because the draft starts at 10.

04:28.333 --> 04:30.709
Just because you're missing it
doesn't mean I have to.

04:30.750 --> 04:32.917
You gotta be there, in person,
to make your picks.

04:32.959 --> 04:35.166
-You're not gonna miss the draft
if you give me ten minutes.

04:35.208 --> 04:38.125
I just want ten minutes, I'm
gonna run in, I'm gonna run out.
Gimme ten minutes.

04:38.166 --> 04:40.291
-I will give you ten minutes
and that's it.
-Thank you.

04:40.333 --> 04:42.542
-I'm gonna...
-So nice.

04:42.583 --> 04:45.875
-[Bill]: I'm very nice.
-[Gerry]: I'll be right out.

04:45.917 --> 04:48.166
-[Robert]: Now, you listen
to me with your ears.

04:48.208 --> 04:51.125
When you waste class time,
you waste everybody's time.

04:51.166 --> 04:53.375
Do I make myself clear?

04:53.417 --> 04:56.875
You think I want to be here on a
Saturday? No!

04:57.834 --> 05:00.250
[Laughs]: I'm just messing
with ya.

05:00.291 --> 05:03.959
Oh my gosh, I love these
principal practice sessions.

05:04.000 --> 05:04.625
-Robert?

05:06.417 --> 05:10.417
What are you doing here?
-Can't a guy get a little
privacy, please?

05:10.458 --> 05:12.625
-Ah...Yeah...

05:12.667 --> 05:14.834
You're in my office though.

05:14.875 --> 05:17.667
-Well then, why don't you finish
disciplining Charles and Zaid?

05:19.333 --> 05:21.667
Take over like you always do!

05:24.125 --> 05:26.041
-[Quietly]: Okay.

05:26.083 --> 05:28.417
-Simon? What are you doing here?
-I'm just going to the library.

05:28.458 --> 05:30.375
-Great! You can cover my
Saturday detention.

05:30.417 --> 05:34.083
-No can do. I work on my Xavier
fan fiction on Saturdays.
-Give me a break.

05:34.125 --> 05:38.792
-It's about the lives and loves
of a ragtag group of unlikely
school chums. You'd like it.

05:38.834 --> 05:41.250
-I wouldn't like it, Simon. Come
on, do me a favour...
-Ahhh.

05:41.291 --> 05:43.875
-You're in there anyway,
just cover it for me.
I have to be somewhere.

05:43.917 --> 05:46.291
-Mmm mmm, I need you in there
as much as those kids, Gerry.

05:46.333 --> 05:49.750
I'm a method writer, Gerry.
I like to take in the sights
and sounds.

05:49.792 --> 05:53.750
Really breathe in the adolescent
angst to make my words come
alive.

05:55.875 --> 05:58.083
-Okay, but you're not going
to sit right there.

05:58.125 --> 06:00.250
-This is my writing nook.
You won't even know I'm here.

06:00.291 --> 06:02.667
-How will I not notice? You're
two feet from me, I can see you.

06:02.709 --> 06:04.917
-Just trying to find my muse,
Gerry.

06:04.959 --> 06:07.792
-Okay, can we just make sure
everyone's here? Alex?
-Yo.

06:07.834 --> 06:10.208
-Amanda-Susan,
where's Amanda-Susan?

06:12.250 --> 06:15.750
-Starts right at 9 o'clock.
-I don't wear a watch.

06:15.792 --> 06:18.250
-[Simon laughs]: Oh my...

06:18.291 --> 06:21.250
-You're sitting in my seat.
-I was here first.

06:21.291 --> 06:23.250
-Get out.
-No, I will not.

06:23.291 --> 06:25.875
-Five, four, three...

06:25.917 --> 06:28.166
-Okay, yup. I'm gone.
I'm gone.

06:30.291 --> 06:32.875
-Ahhh, that's what I thought.
-Are you done?

06:37.125 --> 06:40.959
-[Gerry]: Natalie?
-Present, and accountable
for my actions, sir.

06:41.000 --> 06:45.000
-Can you just calm it down a
bit? We don't need all that
today.

06:45.041 --> 06:47.375
-Peter Thompson?
Where is Peter Thompson?

06:47.417 --> 06:50.542
-Oh yes, that's my boy.
-Where is he?

06:50.583 --> 06:53.291
-I want to say he's down
by the docks, but...

06:53.333 --> 06:55.875
Petey rarely tells me anything.
-Then why are you here?

06:55.917 --> 06:58.041
-Oh, I'm taking his
detention for him.

06:58.083 --> 07:01.792
-[Sighs]: None of this matters,
'cause good news everybody!

07:01.834 --> 07:03.875
I'm letting you go home.
-But we...

07:03.917 --> 07:08.083
-No questions, Natalie.
No questions. I'm letting you go
home, from saturday detention.

07:08.125 --> 07:10.083
I don't want to be here.
You don't want to be here.

07:10.125 --> 07:14.208
All I need you to do is be back
by five o'clock so your parents
can pick...

07:14.250 --> 07:17.166
Your parents or your children
can pick you up.

07:17.208 --> 07:20.917
That's all we need.
Shhh! Our little secret.

07:20.959 --> 07:24.041
-[Sound of door opening]
-Hey everyone! Ms. Mason's here.

07:24.083 --> 07:26.709
[Simon]: Hi Ms. Mason.
-[Lisa]: Hi.

07:26.750 --> 07:28.667
-Well if you're here, why
can't you cover them?

07:28.709 --> 07:32.959
-Because it's your turn, Gerry.
I come in on Saturday's to
get caught up on work,

07:33.000 --> 07:36.125
and check in on detention.
-Don't you have a life?

07:36.166 --> 07:39.959
[Gerry]: No, you don't.
-Enjoy your detention.

07:40.000 --> 07:44.083
-[Simon]: Things are not lookin'
good for old Mr. D.

07:44.125 --> 07:47.291
-[Gerry slams paper down]
-[Simon]: Nightmare.

07:47.333 --> 07:49.250
-Mr. Hunt.
-Mmm hmm?

07:49.291 --> 07:53.125
-You can't dictate to yourself
out loud while your writing.

07:53.166 --> 07:56.208
-Was I talking just there?
-You've done it about
five times.

07:56.250 --> 07:58.750
-Oh my lord.
Oh my lord.

07:58.792 --> 08:01.166
Did I say horror show?

08:01.208 --> 08:05.166
-Oh! Should we write a
five hundred word essay...

08:05.208 --> 08:08.333
About who we think we are?
-Why would you do that, Natalie?

08:08.375 --> 08:12.291
It's a Saturday, give your
head a shake.
[Car horn honks]

08:12.333 --> 08:15.125
-No, no, give me a few
more...Bill! Give me...

08:15.166 --> 08:18.041
[♪ Music]
-[Gerry]: No, Bill! Bill!

08:18.709 --> 08:20.667
[♪ Music]

08:22.542 --> 08:25.667
-[Gerry]: Who took my phone?
-I don't know what you're
talking about, Sir.

08:25.709 --> 08:28.792
-Amanda-Susan, give me my phone.
-I don't have it Sherlock.

08:28.834 --> 08:31.583
-You think you're pretty smart?
Well, let me tell you something.

08:31.625 --> 08:33.875
You're a bum! You're all bums.

08:33.917 --> 08:37.792
Breaking your rules and your
stealing. You keep this up...

08:37.834 --> 08:39.709
You know where you're gonna
end up in five years?

08:39.750 --> 08:42.750
-I don't know about five years,
sir, but I'm being groomed

08:42.792 --> 08:45.250
groomed to take over my dad's
multi-million dollar brokerage
firm.

08:45.291 --> 08:49.583
-[Clears his throat]
Okay, well that sounds
like you're set.

08:49.625 --> 08:52.709
-I'm going to be a partner at
my mother's law firm.

08:52.750 --> 08:56.959
-I plan on leaving Petey's dad
as soon as Petey goes off to
college.

08:57.000 --> 09:00.208
But, shhhh! It's a surprise.

09:00.250 --> 09:02.792
-[Simon]: Talking to no one.

09:02.834 --> 09:04.709
-I don't have to worry.

09:04.750 --> 09:07.709
My parents are rich
and heavy smokers.

09:07.750 --> 09:11.458
I'm a shadow-on-an-x-ray
away from having it all.

09:11.500 --> 09:13.750
-Okay.
-[Simon]: Oh, that's dark.

09:13.792 --> 09:16.291
This is a lot of fun, where
are you going to be, Mr. D?

09:16.333 --> 09:18.583
-Where am I gonna be in
five years?

09:18.625 --> 09:23.333
Teaching.
-Sssss, safe choice. Good.

09:23.375 --> 09:25.750
-But I'm watching you,
Amanda-Susan.

09:28.166 --> 09:30.125
-Watch this.

09:30.166 --> 09:33.291
-What the hell does that mean?
-Well, what the hell does
that mean?

09:35.041 --> 09:37.667
-[Lisa knocks]: Robert?

09:37.709 --> 09:40.250
Do things really have to be
so difficult between us?

09:40.291 --> 09:44.542
We used to be
friend...ly...ish, right?

09:44.583 --> 09:46.583
-Pft, things have changed.
-It's Saturday.

09:46.625 --> 09:51.792
And we're off the clock.
I was thinking maybe we
could unwind a little.

09:51.834 --> 09:54.709
Maybe talk things out?
-Is that an order?

09:54.750 --> 09:59.583
-Robert, you can't spell
'principal' without 'pal'.

09:59.625 --> 10:03.333
-[Lisa laughs]
-You know I'm a sucker for
word play, get in here.

10:03.375 --> 10:05.834
-[Lisa laughs]
-Deal me in, slugger.

10:05.875 --> 10:09.166
-Oh! [Lisa laughs]
-Make it a three finger
stiffy, or go home.

10:09.208 --> 10:13.041
-[Amanda-Susan whistles the
"Colonel Bogey March"]

10:13.083 --> 10:17.041
[Simon joins in]

10:17.083 --> 10:20.208
[Natalie and Alex join in]

10:20.250 --> 10:23.291
[Mrs. Thompson joins in]

10:23.333 --> 10:26.375
-Okay, stop! Stop! Stop! I'm
trying to think here, please.

10:26.417 --> 10:28.542
I gotta get out of here,
I gotta get out of here.

10:28.583 --> 10:31.083
-[Laughs]: Sir?
-What?

10:31.125 --> 10:34.458
-There's no way to get out of
here, without passing
Principal Mason's office.

10:34.500 --> 10:36.667
It can't be done.
-Yeah, it can be done.

10:36.709 --> 10:40.208
'Cause when I leave, I'm gonna
get you guys to cover for me,
In case she comes back in.

10:40.250 --> 10:42.125
-And why would we do that?

10:42.166 --> 10:46.083
-Because, Amanda-Susan,
if I break free, I'll come back
to get you free, okay?

10:46.125 --> 10:48.417
No more questions!

10:50.041 --> 10:52.000
-[Sniffs]

10:52.834 --> 10:54.709
Sweet Vishnu!

10:54.750 --> 10:58.000
That is the smell of pure evil.

10:58.041 --> 11:00.333
[Sniffs]

11:00.375 --> 11:02.625
[Sniffs]
Oh!

11:07.667 --> 11:09.917
Ugh!

11:09.959 --> 11:12.500
Ooof.

11:12.542 --> 11:15.625
So cute, Amanda-Susan.

11:15.667 --> 11:19.917
Come here, fuzzy little
sandwich. Ah hahaha.

11:19.959 --> 11:22.750
[Loud crash]

11:23.583 --> 11:24.667
[Breathes sigh of relief]

11:26.667 --> 11:30.333
-Found my way out. If Ms. Mason
comes in, just tell her I'm
in the washroom.

11:30.375 --> 11:33.458
Cover for me.
That's all I need you to do.

11:33.500 --> 11:35.792
And everything will be fine.

11:35.834 --> 11:38.750
[Gerry]: Good,
good boys and girls.

11:38.792 --> 11:40.834
I'll be back to get you.

11:44.500 --> 11:46.625
And I will get to the draft
for the second round.

11:46.667 --> 11:48.875
And there will still be
good choices.

11:48.917 --> 11:52.709
And I don't have to go back to
those losers and wasting my
Saturday.

11:52.750 --> 11:58.250
So, sorry suckers! That is
how it's gonna play.

11:58.291 --> 12:01.166
[Vent creaks]
-What was that?

12:01.208 --> 12:03.667
-[Gerry]: What the f...?
[There is a thud on the floor]

12:03.709 --> 12:06.083
-Ohhh.
Whoo.

12:07.166 --> 12:09.375
[Strained]: I'm good. I'm good.

12:09.417 --> 12:13.041
-Is this...rock bottom?

12:13.083 --> 12:16.041
-[Quietly]: I didn't get very
far. I did not think that
through.

12:16.083 --> 12:20.417
-Or were there more
indignities to come?

12:20.458 --> 12:22.166
-Shut up, dork.

12:24.000 --> 12:26.625
-[Slurring]: Bobbi did this
thing, just before she
broke my heart...

12:26.667 --> 12:29.709
That really hurt my feelings.

12:29.750 --> 12:31.709
[Robert]:Wanna know what it was?
-Yeah.

12:31.750 --> 12:34.333
-[Robert dry heaves]
-Oh, God. You okay?

12:34.375 --> 12:36.667
You gonna be okay?
-Yeah, I'm fine.

12:36.709 --> 12:38.875
That's what she did, she went...
[Dry heaves again]

12:38.917 --> 12:41.417
-Ew.
-Every time she kissed me...
[dry heaves]

12:41.458 --> 12:43.667
-Oh, bad manners
is what that is.

12:43.709 --> 12:45.917
-It is, bad manners.
-Yeah.

12:45.959 --> 12:48.625
-It's mad banners!
-[Lisa]: Mmm hmm.

12:48.667 --> 12:50.875
-[Excited]: I have a really
great idea.

12:50.917 --> 12:53.709
You and I should tell
each other everything...

12:53.750 --> 12:55.959
That bugs us about each other.

12:56.000 --> 12:58.750
And just air all of our
grievances, put it out
on the table.

12:58.792 --> 13:02.625
And then on Monday...
Boom, we're friends.

13:02.667 --> 13:06.041
-[Robert takes a deep breath]

13:06.083 --> 13:08.041
-Okay.
-You're hair.

13:08.083 --> 13:10.709
-Okay.
-Sometimes when you're
doing something in appropriate

13:10.750 --> 13:13.625
I imagine that it's actually
controlling your mind.

13:13.667 --> 13:16.458
And those shirts?
I mean girls like flowers...

13:16.500 --> 13:18.709
They do, but not on
a mans shirt.

13:18.750 --> 13:21.583
Like, that is the biggest
form of birth control

13:21.625 --> 13:23.834
I have ever seen in my life,
honestly.

13:25.166 --> 13:27.458
-What?! Come on now!

13:27.500 --> 13:29.667
-That looks pretty serious.

13:29.709 --> 13:32.083
Hate for someone to get hurt.

13:32.125 --> 13:34.375
♪ Music

13:34.417 --> 13:36.333
♪ Music

13:36.375 --> 13:39.041
-What? I wanna start wrestling
in a higher weight class.

13:39.083 --> 13:41.792
♪ Music

13:41.834 --> 13:44.291
♪ Music

13:44.333 --> 13:46.709
♪ Music

13:46.750 --> 13:49.208
♪ Music
-The final insult.

13:49.250 --> 13:51.166
-What are we having, Mr. Hunt.

13:51.208 --> 13:54.375
Oh, this is tuna fish with
chopped celery and a...

13:54.417 --> 13:56.583
Soupçon of lemon.

13:56.625 --> 14:00.542
♪ Music

14:00.583 --> 14:02.750
-You terrify me.

14:04.041 --> 14:07.875
-And your neediness just
absolutely repulses people.

14:07.917 --> 14:11.625
And the puns! Nobody puns
the way that you do.

14:11.667 --> 14:16.250
I'd call it a talent if it
didn't make me want
to blow my brains out.

14:16.291 --> 14:19.083
Everytime...Mrah.

14:19.125 --> 14:21.375
[Sighs]

14:21.417 --> 14:23.667
Wow, I feel so much better.

14:23.709 --> 14:28.250
Like this huge weight has been
just lifted off my shoulders.
-Right?

14:28.291 --> 14:32.041
-You should try it! It feels
good. Now it's your turn.

14:32.083 --> 14:35.542
Alright, tell me what you
don't like about me.

14:35.583 --> 14:37.500
Give it to me. I can take it.

14:37.542 --> 14:42.291
-Was I disappointed when you got
the principal job and I didn't?

14:42.333 --> 14:44.917
Yeah, because I felt it should
have been mine.

14:44.959 --> 14:48.166
But, are you qualified
and educated enough?

14:48.208 --> 14:50.166
Absolutely.

14:50.208 --> 14:54.667
And that's why my resentment
is largely offset by...

14:54.709 --> 14:58.750
An enormous feeling of pride.

15:00.583 --> 15:03.000
Of being your colleague.

15:03.041 --> 15:05.333
-I'm just gonna go
get some water.

15:06.875 --> 15:09.667
[Laughs]

15:09.709 --> 15:12.959
[Laughs]: She totally
bought that.

15:13.000 --> 15:15.208
[Laughs]

15:15.250 --> 15:17.250
[Laughs]

15:18.625 --> 15:20.750
-[Alex, voice trembling]:
...and sometimes I feel like

15:20.792 --> 15:24.000
no matter what I do, my parents
never really see me, you know?

15:24.041 --> 15:26.959
[Alex sniffs]
-[Amanda-Susan]:
You think that's bad?

15:27.000 --> 15:29.709
You wanna know what Christmas
is like at the Sullivan house?

15:29.750 --> 15:32.583
[Imitates her dad]: Here you go,
sweetie! An iPhone...

15:32.625 --> 15:36.625
...4S!
-A 4S?! But that doesn't
even have touch ID.

15:36.667 --> 15:39.166
-[Crying]: It doesn't
even have touch ID.

15:39.208 --> 15:41.625
-Hey! It gets better.

15:41.667 --> 15:44.709
-What are you all complaining
about? These aren't problems.

15:44.750 --> 15:46.667
You're young, you're rich...

15:46.709 --> 15:49.333
Some of you are decent looking.

15:49.375 --> 15:51.500
-We should've known you wouldn't
understand real problems.

15:51.542 --> 15:54.542
-You don't think I have real
problems? I have real problems.

15:54.583 --> 15:57.875
I'm not married, I don't have
kids. I don't have a house.

15:57.917 --> 16:00.083
I'm almost forty, okay?

16:00.125 --> 16:03.125
Those are problems. My income
is going down every year.

16:03.166 --> 16:05.333
I don't know how that happens,
but it is.

16:05.375 --> 16:08.166
And the only thing I had to look
forward to, are my weekends.

16:08.208 --> 16:10.750
Until now, and because
of today...

16:10.792 --> 16:13.500
I am missing one of the
biggest days of my life.

16:13.542 --> 16:16.375
My live baseball fantasy draft.

16:16.417 --> 16:18.458
-Wow. That's dark, sir.

16:18.500 --> 16:20.625
-It's not that bad,
I played up the drama a bit.

16:20.667 --> 16:22.792
The car is okay,
the house will come.

16:22.834 --> 16:25.291
No, she's right.
Your life is like a joke.

16:25.333 --> 16:27.208
But no one's laughing.

16:27.250 --> 16:31.166
-Your pathetic story
touched me, sir. Right here.

16:31.208 --> 16:34.250
And that's why we're going
to get you to that draft.

16:34.291 --> 16:37.083
♪ Music
"Don't you forget about me"
By: Simple Minds

16:37.125 --> 16:39.750
Hey, hey, hey ,hey

16:39.792 --> 16:42.667
♪ Ohhh... ♪

16:42.709 --> 16:44.875
-Why are you still here?
Just leave.

16:44.917 --> 16:47.333
-Are you kidding me?
This is great material.

16:47.375 --> 16:50.000
♪ Music

16:50.041 --> 16:52.083
♪ Music

16:52.125 --> 16:55.583
♪ Won't you come see about me? ♪

16:55.625 --> 16:58.041
♪ I'll be alone ♪

16:58.083 --> 17:00.709
♪ Dancing you know it baby ♪

17:00.750 --> 17:04.250
♪ Tell me your troubles
and doubts ♪

17:04.291 --> 17:09.083
♪ Giving me everything
inside and out and ♪

17:09.125 --> 17:11.583
♪ Love's ♪
[Music stops, keys drop]

17:11.625 --> 17:14.834
♪ strange so real in the dark ♪

17:14.875 --> 17:17.000
♪ Think of the tender things ♪

17:17.041 --> 17:19.208
Robert? Is that you?
-[Gerry]: Okay, you know what?

17:19.250 --> 17:21.375
-[Lisa]: I'm sorry for
what I said.
[Music stops]

17:21.417 --> 17:24.333
-She heard us. Alright, this is
my fault we're in this
situation.

17:24.375 --> 17:26.834
We bonded nicely today. I don't
want you guys to get in trouble.

17:26.875 --> 17:29.917
This is my fault. We're not
getting out of here. Go back
to the library.

17:29.959 --> 17:32.083
I'll take the heat with
Ms. Mason.

17:32.125 --> 17:34.250
-I'll do it.
-Are you sure about this, ASS?

17:34.291 --> 17:37.250
-It'll destroy you.
-I don't want him to get caught.

17:37.291 --> 17:39.667
His life sucks enough already.
-[Simon]: Ohhh.

17:39.709 --> 17:42.750
-Okay, that works! Go! Let's go.
-[Whispers]: Oh yeah!

17:42.792 --> 17:44.917
-Amanda-Susan.
[♪ Music]

17:44.959 --> 17:49.291
-You're such a trouble maker,
you are in big trouble. Come on.

17:50.208 --> 17:52.083
[♪ Music]

17:52.125 --> 17:55.208
-Hey Mr. Duncan.
Look who I found.

17:55.250 --> 17:58.333
Trying to leave the suprem...
School premises.

17:59.792 --> 18:01.667
-Amanda-Susan!

18:01.709 --> 18:04.291
I let you go to the bathroom
and this is what you do?

18:04.333 --> 18:06.250
Unbelievable.

18:06.291 --> 18:08.458
-[Slurring, slightly]: And as
a punishment, okay?

18:08.500 --> 18:10.959
I gonna make you do a
two thousand word essay...

18:11.000 --> 18:13.917
on why you're in
Saturday detention.

18:13.959 --> 18:16.583
-Sure, Principal Mason.
-Good.

18:16.625 --> 18:18.750
-Oh, Miss?
One question.

18:18.792 --> 18:23.166
Should I say you were
drinking on school grounds,
or did you show up drunk?

18:23.208 --> 18:25.208
-[Quietly]: Ha.

18:26.291 --> 18:29.667
-Well played. You're free to go.
-Later losers.

18:29.709 --> 18:32.750
-Don't mess with the ASS.
You get the hooves.

18:32.792 --> 18:35.667
-Don't do that. It looks
stupid on you.

18:37.041 --> 18:40.166
-[Lisa]: Hey Robert, ummm, I am
just leaving for the day.

18:40.208 --> 18:42.583
I just wanted to make
sure you're okay.

18:42.625 --> 18:44.750
-I'm fine.
-[Lisa sighs]

18:44.792 --> 18:49.375
Robert, can we just clean slate
our clean slate?

18:49.417 --> 18:51.750
Do you think we can still
be friends on Monday?

18:51.792 --> 18:54.125
-Oh my gosh.

18:57.959 --> 19:00.375
Nope!
-No?

19:02.500 --> 19:04.542
-[Gerry sighs]

19:04.583 --> 19:07.208
-Goodbye Mr. Duncan! Thanks for
making today super fun.

19:07.250 --> 19:09.458
-Natalie, why are you
always so positive?

19:09.500 --> 19:11.750
And how did you end up getting a
Saturday detention?

19:11.792 --> 19:15.041
-I just had a real hard time
after losing the election,
ya know?

19:15.083 --> 19:17.667
So, I went into the
student council office,

19:17.709 --> 19:19.875
peed in a cup and sprayed
it everywhere.

19:19.917 --> 19:22.750
-What!?
-I had to mark my territory,
didn't I?

19:22.792 --> 19:26.667
-[Car horn honks]
-Oh, there's my mom. Bu-bye!

19:26.709 --> 19:29.792
-I had to burn that carpet.
-Shoulda burned the whole room.

19:29.834 --> 19:34.000
-...and then I realized, I was
the one seeing everyone in
the simplest terms,

19:34.041 --> 19:36.291
in the most convenient
definitions.

19:36.333 --> 19:40.542
It turns out, each of us is
a brain, and a jock.

19:40.583 --> 19:44.792
And a basket case and a
princess and a criminal.

19:44.834 --> 19:49.458
We're all criminals.

19:49.500 --> 19:51.625
-That's how you've been
wasting your weekends?

19:51.667 --> 19:53.667
-Ya like it?
-No, I don't like it.

19:53.709 --> 19:57.625
How are we all jocks?
I'm the only jock in this
whole group today.

19:57.667 --> 20:00.125
You are certainly not a jock.

20:00.166 --> 20:03.250
And Mrs. Thompson...
She's just nuts.

20:03.291 --> 20:05.917
So that's terrible writing.

20:05.959 --> 20:08.583
-All good notes.
-You ready to go, Simon?

20:08.625 --> 20:11.792
-Oh boy.
-Have you been doing
squats, Gerry?

20:11.834 --> 20:15.125
Your thigh muscles
look enormous.

20:15.166 --> 20:18.583
[Angela giggles]
-Yeah, you're gonna
need bigger pants.

20:18.625 --> 20:23.375
[♪ Music]
-Obviously, I've been doing
squats.

20:23.417 --> 20:26.417
[♪ Music]

20:26.959 --> 20:30.166
[♪ Music]

20:30.208 --> 20:32.333
-Finally! I thought you
forgot about me.

20:32.375 --> 20:34.667
-Why don't you just walk?
It's twenty minutes away.

20:34.709 --> 20:36.625
-'Cause you said you were
coming back to get me.

20:36.667 --> 20:39.667
-The draft went late. I tried
to call you, but your phone
was in the car.

20:39.709 --> 20:42.291
-Ah, that's where my phone is.
Did you get my picks?

20:42.333 --> 20:44.250
-No.
-No?

20:44.291 --> 20:46.667
-What was...What's with the...
-What? That?

20:46.709 --> 20:49.083
-Yeah.
-I was excited to see you,
I've been waiting.

20:49.125 --> 20:51.166
-That's your pose for you're
excited to see me?

20:51.208 --> 20:55.834
-This is embarrassing,
everything you're doing right
now. You look like an idiot.

20:55.875 --> 20:58.667
-Pft. Tell that to Judd Nelson.
